{"id":"2305.06975","submitter":"Matheus Ara\\'ujo Marques","authors":"I. Andrade, D. Bazeia, M.A. Marques and R. Menezes","title":"Maxwell-scalar system and scalar field with impurities","comments":"22 pages, 6 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this work, we investigate Maxwell-scalar model that couples the scalar and\ngauge fields through the electric permittivity and another model, in which the\nscalar field lives in the presence of impurities. By considering a single\nspatial dimension, we determine the conditions under which the model with\nimpurities can be seen as an effective model for the Maxwell-scalar system,\nmaking them have the same solutions, energy-momentum tensor and stability. The\nresults show that the impurity can be used to describe the presence of a charge\ndensity. We use this correspondence to show that the impurity-free case, which\nsupports minimum energy configurations, is related to the case of point\ncharges. Moreover, we investigate a class of impurities that modify the core of\nthe solutions and find the corresponding charge densities and electric fields.\nThe asymptotic behavior in terms of the impurity is also studied, leading to\nlong range or quasi-compact structures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 May 2023 17:00:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-12"}
